{"word":"H4302 - מַטָּע - maṭṭâʻ - mat-taw' - Plant","slug":"H4302","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מַטָּע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>maṭṭâʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mat-taw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Plant"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05D8;&#x05BC;&#x05E2; - mat&#x0323;t&#x0323;a&#x0302;&#x201B;</b> - <i>mat-taw'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H5193\">H5193</a>; something <i>planted</i>, that is, the place (a <i>garden</i> or vineyard), or the thing (a <i>plant</i>, figuratively of men); by implication the act, <i>planting: - </i>plant (-ation, -ing)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5193\">H5193</a>, <a href=\"#/H5194\">H5194</a>, <a href=\"#/H5195\">H5195</a>, <a href=\"#/H5196\">H5196</a>"}]}